    "long_instructions": "##  🔍Teacher Tip\r\nUse the prompts below to explore how to mitigate bias while using AI Chat Lab. While you're working *try to identify the types of bias you're seeing in the responses including stereotyping, assuming one identity, leaving out other perspectives, and using language that isn't inclusive*.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## **Refine Prompts to Mitigate Bias**\r\n\r\n1. Choose a prompt to ask AI Chat.\r\n    * Recommend 5 foods\r\n    * Recommend 5 hairstyles\r\n    * Recommend 5 games\r\n    * Recommend 5 clothing styles\r\n2. Review the response and notice:\r\n    * What's showing up in the response?\r\n    * What's missing or assumed?\r\n    * Would this recommendation work for *you*?\r\n3. Choose a rewritten prompt that includes a **specific group, style, or context**.\r\n    * \"Recommend 5 foods\" → \"Recommend 5 traditional Filipino foods\"\r\n    * \"Recommend 5 hairstyles\" → \"Recommend 5 protective hairstyles for curly hair\"\r\n    * \"Recommend 5 games\" → \"Recommend 5 games that don't need a lot of equipment\"\r\n    * \"Recommend 5 clothing styles\" → \"Recommend 5 modest clothing styles for teen girls\"\r\n4. Ask the refined version of the prompt in AI Chat.\r\n5. Compare the responses. *What changed? What stayed the same?*\r\n",
    "name_suffix": "_2025"
